0                                   1289      56.     ********************************************************************
                                    1290      57.     *                                                                  *
                                    1291      58.     *   Filedump fixit list, for the next programmer to work with      *
                                    1292      59.     *                        this module.                              *
                                    1293      60.     *                                                                  *
                                    1294      61.     ********************************************************************
                                    1295      62.     *                                                                  *
                                    1296      63.     *  1.  Make the number of file system IOB's dynamic instead of     *
                                    1297      64.     *      an assembled set symbol.                                    *
                                    1298      65.     *                                                                  *
                                    1299      66.     *  2.  Add ESTAE exit for dump/read subtasks to release I/O        *
                                    1300      67.     *      buffers.  The dump is getting pretty damn big.              *
                                    1301      68.     *                                                                  *
                                    1302      69.     *  3.  Nice termination after abend.  Terminate remaining subtasks *
                                    1303      70.     *      and don't start any more!                                   *
                                    1304      71.     *                                                                  *
                                    1305      72.     *  4.  Modify all SYSOUT=$ dynamic allocation to general subroutine*
                                    1306      73.     *                                                                  *
                                    1307      74.     *  5.  Take a major pass at renumbering all the messages.  There's *
                                    1308      75.     *      no reason for the scheme at this point.                     *
                                    1309      76.     *                                                                  *
                                    1310      77.     *  6.  Implement dump trace from ESTAE exit.                       *
                                    1311      78.     *                                                                  *
                                    1312      79.     *  7.  Check code dependancies for 2k ORVYL user block length.  Add*
                                    1313      80.     *      option in control file for variable length header and data. *
                                    1314      81.     *                                                                  *
                                    1315      82.     *  8.  Code dynamic io rate setting for various time of day values.*
                                    1316      83.     *      Mainly for RLG incremental dump to keep the operator happy. *
                                    1317      84.     *                                                                  *
                                    1318      85.     *  9.  Recode dump tape i/o to use BSAM for better control over    *
                                    1319      86.     *      tape volume switching and statistics.                       *
                                    1320      87.     *                                                                  *
                                    1321      88.     * 10.  Add code on mainline control to start the directory and     *
                                    1322      89.     *      verify portion of a full dump.                              *
                                    1323      90.     *                                                                  *
                                    1324      91.     * 11.  Enable code to restart failure dump segments after a tape   *
                                    1325      92.     *      I/O error.                                                  *
                                    1326      93.     *                                                                  *
                                    1327      97.     *                                                                  *
                                    1328      98.     ********************************************************************

0                                   1330     100.              MACRO
                                    1331     101.     &L       VTRACE &SAVE=,&REG=,&OFF=NO
                                    1332     102.              LCLA  &P,&Q
                                    1333     103.              AIF   ('&L' EQ '').NOL
                                    1334     104.     &L       LABEL ,
                                    1335     105.     .NOL     ANOP
                                    1336     106.              AIF   ('&OFF' EQ 'YES').NSV1
                                    1337     107.              AIF   ('&REG' EQ 'NO').NOREG
                                    1338     108.              STM   14,1,0(R13)             ***CHECK***
                                    1339     109.     .NOREG   ANOP
                                    1340     110.     &P       SETA  2
                                    1341     111.     .LOOP    AIF   ('&SYSLIST(&P)' EQ '').NEXT
                                    1342     112.              AIF   ('&SYSLIST(&P)' EQ '*').NEXT MVC STOPPER
                                    1343     113.              AIF   ('&SYSLIST(&P)'(1,1) EQ '@').CREG
                                    1344     114.              AIF   ('&SYSLIST(&P)'(1,1) NE '(').MVC
                                    1345     115.              ST    &SYSLIST(&P),0    ***CHECK *** TRCTEMP-8+&P*4
                                    1346     116.              AGO   .NEXT
                                    1347     117.     .CREG    ANOP
                                    1348     118.              STMC  &SYSLIST(&P)(2,8),&SYSLIST(&P)(2,8),0 TRCTEMP-8+&P*4
                                    1349     119.              AGO   .NEXT
                                    1350     120.     .MVC     ANOP
                                    1351     121.     &Q       SETA  &P
                                    1352     122.     .LUP     AIF   (&P GE 5).LUPEND
                                    1353     123.              AIF   ('&SYSLIST(&P+1)' NE '').LUPEND
                                    1354     124.     &P       SETA  &P+1
                                    1355     125.              AGO   .LUP
                                    1356     126.     .LUPEND  AIF   ('&SYSLIST(&Q)' NE 'CTSTCK').NOSTCK
                                    1357     127.              STCK  0(R13)  ***  CHECK  ***  CTSTCK
                                    1358     128.     .NOSTCK  MVC   TRCTEMP-8+&Q*4((&P-&Q+1)*4),&SYSLIST(&Q)
                                    1359     129.     .NEXT    ANOP
                                    1360     130.     &P       SETA  &P+1
                                    1361     131.              AIF   (&P LE 5).LOOP
                                    1362     132.              AIF   ('&SAVE' EQ 'NO').NSV
                                    1363     133.              AIF   ('&SAVE' EQ '').SAVCT
                                    1364     134.              LR    &SAVE,R9
                                    1365     135.              AGO   .NSV
                                    1366     136.     .SAVCT   ANOP

                                    1371     141.              AIF   ('&SAVE' EQ 'NO').NSV1

                                    1374     144.              AGO   .NSV1

                                    1376     146.              L     R9,0  **  CHECK **  TRCRSAV9
                                    1377     147.     .NSV1    MEXIT
                                    1378     148.              MEND

                                   13592  1  335.                COPY  IOB
                                   13593  1          =***********************************************************************
                                   13594  1          =*                                                                     *
                                   13595  1          =*                    STANDARD SECTION OF THE IOB                      *
                                   13596  1          =*                                                                     *
                                   13597  1          =***********************************************************************
-                                         1
 000000                            13599  1          =IOBSTDRD   DS    0D
0000000                            13601  1          =IOBFLAG1   DS    B -       FLAG BYTE
                                   13602  1          =IOBDATCH   EQU   X'80' --- DATA CHAINING USED IN CHANNEL PROGRAM
                                   13603  1          =IOBCMDCH   EQU   X'40' --- COMMAND CHAINING USED IN CHANNEL PROGRAM
                                   13604  1          =IOBERRTN   EQU   X'20' --- ERROR ROUTINE IS IN CONTROL
                                   13605  1          =IOBRPSTN   EQU   X'10' --- DEVICE IS TO BE REPOSITIONED
                                   13606  1          =IOBCYCCK   EQU   X'08' --- CYCLIC REDUNDANCY CHECK NEEDED(TAPE ONLY)
                                   13607  1          =IOBFCREX   EQU   X'08' --- FETCH COMMAND RETRY EXIT (DIRECT ACCESS ONLY)
                                   13608  1          =IOBIOERR   EQU   X'04' --- I/O ERROR HAS OCCURRED

 003EE8 D707 2008 2000 00008 00000 31210  3 3562.                    XC    @SR+8(8),@SR              the

 003EF8                            31218  2 3565.                  END   ,

                                   36505  1 4460.     *                                                                  *
                                   36506  1 4461.     *    Main dump loop - Chain thru IOB's (circular chain) until      *

                                   36508  1 4463.     *    signals end of file.  The control blocks are then             *

0                                  42306    5359.     ********************************************************************
                                   42307    5360.     *                                                                  *
                                   42308    5361.     *   Allocate an incremental dump data set from the incremental     *
                                   42309    5362.     *   dump pool.  Since we're not the only thing running when we     *
                                   42310    5362.1    *   run out of space, pause and refresh the pool control blocks.   *
                                   42311    5362.2    *   If we have to refresh more than twice i think we got           *
                                   42312    5362.3    *   problems.                                                      *
                                   42313    5363.     *                                                                  *
                                   42314    5363.01   ********************************************************************
                                   42315    5363.02   *                                                                  *
                                   42316    5363.1    *        1.  Allocate and link incremental data set control block. *
                                   42317    5363.2    *        2.  Find pool control block with most space available.    *
                                   42318    5363.21   *            If the pool order option is in effect select from     *
                                   42319    5363.22   *            the first pool volume which has sufficient space.     *
                                   42320    5363.3    *        3.  Allocate incremental data set.  on error recompute    *
                                   42321    5363.4    *            space available pool control blocks and retry.        *
                                   42322    5363.5    *        4.  Update incremental data set control block with        *
                                   42323    5363.6    *            volume and number of blocks.                          *
                                   42324    5363.7    *                                                                  *
                                   42325    5364.     ********************************************************************
